**Elasticsearch version**: 5.0.0-rc1

**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:
Currently we [default scripts to lang=painless and treat the parameter as optional in many places](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/20122#issuecomment-244337340).  We [say it's not required](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/5.0/script-processor.html) in the Ingest Script Processor, but we still throw `"reason": "[lang] required property is missing"` if you don't include the parameter.  I think this one just got missed when we did the defaults switch.

**Steps to reproduce**:

```
POST _ingest/pipeline/_simulate
{
  "pipeline" :
  {
    "description": "_description",
    "processors": [
      {
        "script": {
          "inline":"ctx.hi = 'hello';"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "docs": [
    {
      "_index": "shanetest",
      "_type": "shanetest",
      "_id": "1",
      "_source": {
        "field_a": 3
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Beginning from 5.0.0-beta1 SearchSourceBuilder adds an "ext" field. This way count queries can not work with queries generated using SearchSourceBuilder as ext is not supported. 

Empty query by just creating new SearchSourceBuilder looks now like this:

{
  "ext": {}
}

_search will return results, _count will return 

{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "parsing_exception",
        "reason": "request does not support [ext]",
        "line": 2,
        "col": 3
      }
    ],
    "type": "parsing_exception",
    "reason": "request does not support [ext]",
    "line": 2,
    "col": 3
  },
  "status": 400
}

